# Day 244: Off the grid piano setup

This is enough for just playing:
- Korg microPIANO, on NiMH batteries
- Korg DS-1H damper pedal

For this recording, I used these additional items:
- a BOSS RC-202 looper, not for looping, but so that the piano output can go to the camera more directly, rather than via a mike
- mobile power: Anker PowerCore III Elite 26000mAh 87W
- a USB-C to 9V trigger
- a 9V polarity inverter cable

